title: Show HN: Nordic Game Jam 2023
text:
Hi HN :-)

We are hosting our Nordic Game Jam 2023, 13-16 April, at Aalborg University, Copenhagen.

Nordic Game Jam has been running since 2006, it is an annual, 48 hours, game jam with a focus on bringing the games industry together, both veteran and hobbyist, in a playful, experimental and educational form.

We just had our first talk announcement: "Porting your Unity knowledge to Godot Engine", which fits perfectly if you are interested in the new developments of Godot Engine. We will be announcing many more activities throughout this month.

I have been part of the organiser team for 3 years now. It is completely volunteer driven. It was though to get through COVID as we highly appreciate the in-person culture. Incredibly grateful to be back again!

I am merely sharing because we tend to get a bit limited to the nordic countries (no wonder!), but we had quite a few participants from other countries who loved coming and getting a sneak peek into how the Nordic games industry looks.

Show HN: Open-Source ChatGPT UI – ChatWithMe.chat
text:
site: https://www.chatwithme.chat/

code: https://github.com/kierangilliam/chatwithme.chat

Features

- Bring your own API token

- Chat history and API token is stored in your browser, not any 3rd party server

- Pay only for what you use

- Open source

- Uses gpt-3.5-turbo model

It will ask for your OpenAI access token. This token is never sent to a third-party server, only OpenAI.

It does not have feature parity with ChatGPT but it gives you the basics.

Ask HN: Why some people do work much faster than others?
text:
Do you have that feeling what you see that someone posted "Hey, checkout my landing/video/product/whatever. Spent a couple of ours in the evening".

While you're struggling with getting a freaking checkbox work correctly in your HTML for hours?

Either

1. People exaggerate a lot 2. There is some difference between who can work productively and do things fast (and also with good quality, I don't take into account rubbish code) and who spend much more time.

But I cannot get it. I'm the same programmer, as many, and I've built a lot of apps in my life. But it looks like it takes much more time for me.

Imposter syndrome? People exaggerating? Or maybe some focus, concentration techniques used by others? ADHD?

title: Show HN: Castled – No-Code Segmentation Engine on Top of Your Data Warehouse
text:
In the last 12 months, we have spent a lot of time optimising queries for our Segment/Audience builder, which is part of our warehouse-first marketing platform. To give you more context, the Audience builder in Castled allows non-technical folks to create user segments on the data warehouse without using SQL and without involving data engineers.

Now, this concept is nothing new. Existing Reverse ETL solutions already provide this capability, but the problem is that the feature is available only in their expensive "enterprise" package. This makes it difficult for an average marketer or product manager to leverage this capability.

Today, we are excited to announce that we are making our Audience Builder available as a standalone product - Castled Audiences. With Audiences, you can create custom user segments in your warehouse and send them to a destination of your choice. Also, this feature is available in our Starter package - no hidden conditions applicable. The cost is the same if you are sending it to 1 destination or 20. Here is a demo:

https://www.loom.com/share/4e10b4e80c8b43efbb29e2c287d35744

Feel free to email me at frank@castled.io, if you want to give it a try. If you do not find the destination you are looking for - Let us know and we will get it added within a day or two.

Show HN: GPT3.5-powered Relationship guidance app
text:
Hellooo NH,

I have created an app that helps couples establish deep communication from the early stages of their relationship. The app gives you a question and an action for your date, then afterwards app sends you a self-reflection question and asks for your feedback on how the date has gone.

And we used GPT-3 to personalize questions and actions to a couple. And today I've integrated the app with GPT 3.5 Turbo to see whether there is any change in the quality. And it's much cooler! GPT 3.5 can pick up the couple's context much better and produce a more profound personalization with smaller prompt!

Here are the links to Apple Store (https://apps.apple.com/no/app/nemlys/id1662262055) and Google Play (https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.nemlys.app)

Here is a more detailed description about what we do in the previous post https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=34955950

Show HN: Compare 259 paid proxy plans across 19 data points
text:
This project aims to aggregate data about available paid proxy plans to assist with comparing pricing and features. Nearly all of the displayed data is obtained automatically from the proxy providers (it scrapes the scrapers' websites/APIs every few hours).

Eventually I would like to automate testing the proxies of each provider for things like IP reputation, blocks, speed, and uptime to see if their services actually match their claims.

I'm planning on adding nearly 20 more proxy providers, please comment if there is a particular provider you'd like to see included.
